decision_conditions:
The development hereby permitted shall be begun no later than the  expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: In order to comply with the requirements of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990.
description: Demolish existing structures. Erection of one part 3/part 6 storey and one part 3/part 5 storey building to provide 52 residential flats with associated highway, cycle parking spaces, landscaping and communal amenity space. (AMENDED DESCRIPTION). (Summary).
